column9: Senior Vice President - Financial Advisor, Consulting Group&lt

column1: Bill is a Senior Vice President-Financial Advisor at RBC Wealth Management. His experience in financial services and investment analysis spans 33 years. He is a New Mexico native and graduate of Tucumcari High School. Bill graduated on the Dean’s List from the US Military Academy at West Point and attained his M.A. in History from the University of North Carolina. After completing the Army’s Ranger and Airborne Schools, he served as a field artillery officer and battery commander in Germany, Vietnam, and at Fort Carson, Colorado. He taught history to cadets at West Point from 1974 to 1978 while on the faculty of the Military Academy. After eleven years of active service, Bill returned to Albuquerque and began his career as a financial advisor in 1978. Bill and Karla are involved in numerous community endeavors including the United Way, Joy Junction, and the Lobo Club. They also enjoy traveling around the country with their ten grandchildren.

column1: The formula Barron's uses to rank advisors is proprietary. It has three major components: assets managed, revenue produced and quality of practice. Investment returns are not a component of the rankings because an advisor's returns are dictated largely by the risk tolerance of clients. The quality-of-practice component includes an evaluation of each advisor's regulatory record.

After graduating from San Diego State University with a degree in communications, Karla worked in a public relations agency. A chance encounter landed her an interview at Merrill Lynch and she entered the financial services industry in 2005. She has always worked with highly successful teams and in time became a registered Client Service Associate and joined the Souligny Wells Group where she is now focused on marketing, client services and daily administrative duties.

Originally from Mexico, Karla comes from a big family and takes great pride in her heritage. She enjoys spending time with her husband, Alberto, their dog and her extended family. Having taken up photography as a hobby, Karla enjoys being outdoors and capturing special moments with her camera.

column3: Bill Cariker understands what lies at the core of this important work that he does every day for his clients at RBC Wealth Management: “I’m tasked with being a good steward with my client’s money. It’s as simple as that,” he says. “They’re counting on me to get it right.”&lt
column7: Bill was born in Denver but grew up in mostly rural south Texas. His father and mother ran Varner-Hogg State Park, a 52 acre spread near West Columbia, Texas for over a quarter century. He learned from both of them the value of finishing the task at hand, no matter how difficult, and that has served him well at every station in life.&lt
column11: He graduated from Southwestern University with a degree in Biology and Chemistry. He would spend a few years with Dow Chemical as a Technical Service Chemist before embarking on a 23-year career with Merrill Lynch. While at Merrill Lynch, he took on the 2-year task of getting his CFP, or Certified Financial Planner designation.&lt
column15: Along the way, Bill also found the time to complete an MBA at Texas A&amp
column21: He arrived at RBC Wealth Management a little over three years ago, and he admits with a healthy dose of humility that he is one of the lucky ones, because this role gives him a chance to do what he does best every day. “I love to learn, and I really like sharing what I learn with my clients,” he says. “This is a partnership, and the good people I&amp
column23: work for need a steady hand on the wheel. I believe I provide that.”&lt
column27: He has always admired country doctors, those selfless souls who dedicate their lives to the health of their communities. His grandfather was a doctor, and one of his mentors was as well. Bill once even thought about going into the medical field himself.&lt
column31: Instead, he has devoted his life to the financial health of his clients, and frankly, he cares as much as any physician ever cared for a patient. His knowledge allows&amp
column33: him to administer preventative medicine to keep their portfolios healthy and&amp
column39: It’s a mission he relishes, and it too has some unforgettable moments. “I’ve had people invite me to a house warming and stand up in front of everyone and say ‘This is the house that Bill made possible.’ And, I get to see parents send their kids off to college without all the financial stress that often accompanies it, just because we made good decisions along the way. It doesn’t get any better than that.” &lt
column43: Bill is married to Lynne, and they live in Austin, Texas.&lt

column9: First Vice President - Financial Advisor, Senior Portfolio Manager - Portfolio Focus&lt

I provide individual and corporate investors a broad spectrum of financial services with an emphasis on specialized portfolio management. With over 30 years of investment experience, I combine my financial knowledge with a dedication to my clients’ individual needs. By developing a close working relationship with my clients, I help create portfolios that are a true reflection of each client’s investment temperament and financial objectives.&lt
column23: With over 30 years of experience, I have been helping clients achieve their financial goals. I specialize in creating retirement spending plans for clients entering their retirement age by using a customized approach to developing and managing their wealth. I help build financial independence and a comfortable retirement. I graduated from the University of California, Berkeley, in 1977 with a bachelor’s degree in political science. Today my professional registrations include the Series 7, 8, 63 and 65 licenses. Through an internal RBC Wealth Management program, I earned the Accredited Wealth Manager designation. The program builds on the fundamentals of wealth management with a focus on advanced knowledge and skills necessary for working with high net worth clients. I am also a member of the IAG (Investment Advisor Group) Advisory Council, whose mission is to provide strategic guidance and input on how best to grow, service, and support fee-based business.&lt

column11: I reside in downtown San Jose with my wife, Susan, and have two married daughters and two grandchildren. I also enjoy traveling the world with my family, and golfing. I am a CAL football fanatic and a Sharks, Giants and 49ers fan.&lt

column3: For over 24 years I have dedicated my career to assisting my clients in planning for financial independence. If you were to ask me how my financial advisory practice is different, or where my area of specialization lies, it is that I specialize in working with clients who are going through financial transitions. From planning for or transitioning into retirement, a job or career change, preparing financially for a college education, or selling the family business, to helping clients who are divorced or widowed, my specialty lies in helping clients who are facing a new and often uncertain financial future. By assisting my clients with a well thought out plan, I can help them address the often complex and confusing issues surrounding investments, insurance, retirement, estate, and divorce planning.&lt

I am currently accepting new clients, and would welcome the opportunity to speak with you. So, if you or someone close might be facing a financial transition in their life and are in need of a caring and knowledgeable professional advisor to help them navigate an uncertain future, please &lt
column7: . There is no fee for an introductory consultation with me and everything we discuss is strictly confidential.&lt

column13: Managing Director - Financial Advisor, Senior Consulting Group&lt

column3: Brian began his career as a financial advisor with Ferris, Baker Watts, Inc. in 1991. During his tenure at Ferris, Baker Watts, Inc., Brian had the pleasure of working directly with Julius Westheimer, who was widely recognized as a renowned financial advisor in the Baltimore metropolitan area.&amp
column9: With over twenty four years of investment experience, Brian has attained the Accredited Wealth Manager designation through the Estate and Wealth Strategies Institute of Michigan State University. After completing the extensive curriculum required, Brian earned the certification of CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER™ (CFP®). He is licensed by the Maryland Insurance Administration and his industry licenses include the Series 7, 31, 63 and 65. Brian is also an Accredited Investment Fiduciary (AIF®), which represents his advanced training and competency in the subject of fiduciary responsibility.&lt
column13: Aside from his notable standing within RBC Wealth Management, Brian has earned accolades and respect within the financial industry. He has been recognized by Barron's as one of the Top 1,200 Financial Advisors in the country in 2014, 2015 and 2016 and by Barron's as one of the Top 1,000 Financial Advisors since 2010. Brian has also been cited as an Influential Marylander by The Daily Record. From the time RBC Wealth Management acquired Ferris Baker Watts, Brian has been a member of the firm's Chairman's Council, an honor bestowed on the top 150 Financial Advisors of RBC Wealth Management Financial Advisors.&amp
column19: Brian is a financial commentator on Baltimore’s WBAL news radio and television network. You can listen to him every Saturday morning at 10:00 AM on WBAL Radio hosting the ""Brian Kroneberger Financial Hour."" If you miss him on Saturday you can catch him weekdays at 7:50 AM on WBAL radio providing timely market insight during his ""Money Report."" In addition to Brian’s daily presence on WBAL radio, he makes frequent appearances on WBAL Television.&lt
column23: Brian currently serves as the Chair on the Investment Committee for the&amp
column27: Catholic Community Foundation of the Archdiocese of Baltimore&lt
column29: . In addition, he is a Board of Trustee for&amp
column41: Born and raised in Baltimore, Maryland, Brian attended Calvert Hall College High School and graduated from Loyola University with a Bachelor of Business Administration in Finance. Brian was a Three Time All-American lacrosse player at Loyola University and played eight years professionally with the Baltimore Thunder of the Major Indoor Lacrosse League. He is a member of both The Greater Baltimore Lacrosse Chapter and the Loyola University Hall of Fame. Brian is married with three children.&lt

column1: The formula Barron's uses to rank advisors is proprietary. It has three major components: assets managed, revenue produced and quality of practice. Investment returns are not a component of the rankings because an advisor's returns are dictated largely by the risk tolerance of clients. The quality-of-practice component includes an evaluation of each advisor's regulatory record.
